Advanced Docker Compose 芒聙聰 Handling Dependencies in Multi-Service Applications
Objectives
Design and implement a health-aware Docker Compose stack in which each service starts only after its upstream dependencies pass readiness checks
Implement graceful failure handling so that the application layer degrades predictably when a backing service becomes unavailable
Validate the full dependency chain through automated failure injection and recovery testing
Prerequisites
Comfort working on the Linux command line: navigating directories, editing files with a terminal editor, and reading command output
Familiarity with how web applications communicate with databases and cache layers at the network level
Understanding of what a container is and why startup order matters when one process depends on another being ready
Lab Environment
You will work on a dedicated AWS EC2 Ubuntu instance provided by Al Nafi. The instance has a base Ubuntu installation; you will install all required tools in Task 1.

